properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued March 1 at 5:09AM MST until March 1 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...Winter Weather Advisories for Portions of Central and Southern
Wyoming through this evening...

.Snow will occur today into this evening. The snow is likely to
persist across southern Wyoming through late this evening. The
combination of snow and wind could create hazardous travel in some
locations.

* WHAT...Snow. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 12 inches. Winds
gusting as high as 35 mph in open areas.

* WHERE...Wind River Mountains East.

* WHEN...Through 11 PM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult across South Pass,
due to blowing snow reducing visibility. Cold wind chills, as
low as negative 20 in the mountains, could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM MST THIS EVENING
